09/05/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish air forces carried out an operation against targets of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in northern Iraq on Friday (May 7th) after a rebel attack that claimed the lives of two Turkish soldiers, the army said in a statement.
A group of 25 members of the PKK attacked a military checkpoint in the Hakkari province earlier in the day.
Five Kurdish rebels were killed in the clashes.
(Reuters, AFP, Zaman - 08/05/10)
